HEADWORD: Twelfth-second
<hw>Twelfth"-sec`ond</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A unit for the measurement of small intervals
of time, such that 10<exp>12</exp> (ten trillion) of these units make
one second.</def><-- now picosecond. But-- should be thousand trillion,
no??? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

